1 -- Open the virtual box and install Ubuntu OS in it.
2 -- Power off the VM which you want to add virtual box.
3 -- Then right click on that VM, select settings.
4 -- Then click on storage, find controller IDE.
5 -- In the top right, find add hard disk icon, the pop-up window displays. 
6 -- On that window, select create new disk and then click next and finish. 
7 -- the find attributes icon, hard disk as IDE secondary enclave.
